      "id": "new-blog-static-site-generator",
      "title": "New blog - a new blog, a new static site generator ...ish",
      "date": "2020-10-19T17:22:06",
      "content": "Welcome%20to%20my%20new%20blog!%20I%20haven't%20imported%20my%20%5Bold%20blog%20posts%5D(http://csiew.github.io/blog)%20to%20this%20new%20one.%20This%20new%20blog%20uses%20a%20successor%20to%20my%20static%20site%20generator%20script%20%5Bmd2magic%5D(http://github.com/csiew/md2magic)%20to%20help%20with%20importing%20and%20indexing%20posts.%0A%0AThe%20new%20script%20is%20also%20written%20in%20Python.%20However%20I%20am%20now%20using%20JSON%20files%20for%20its%20configuration%20and%20post%20manifest.%20This%20was%20inspired%20by%20my%20work%20on%20%5BBiscuitWM%5D(http://github.com/csiew/biscuitwm)%20which%20also%20uses%20a%20JSON%20file%20for%20configuration.%0A%0AYou%20can%20view%20the%20script%20in%20all%20its%20glory/horror%20on%20the%20%5Brepository%5D(http://github.com/csiew/website)%20of%20this%20site%20(under%20the%20name%20%5B*statgen.py*%5D(https://github.com/csiew/website/blob/master/statgen.py)%20in%20the%20root%20directory).%20I%20will%20perhaps%20create%20a%20separate%20repository%20for%20this%20script%20once%20it%20has%20reached%20a%20point%20of%20maturity.%0A%0AUnlike%20md2magic,%20it%20is%20not%20responsible%20for%20converting%20markdown%20files%20into%20HTML.%20Like%20I%20mentioned%20earlier,%20it's%20now%20more%20of%20an%20indexing%20tool%20that%20allows%20your%20site%20to%20have%20a%20readily-available%20list%20of%20your%20posts%20with%20some%20metadata."
  },
  {
      "id": "building-a-webdev-automation-tool",
      "title": "Building a webdev automation tool",
      "date": "2021-02-05T14:58:08",
      "content": "As%20of%20late,%20I've%20been%20attempting%20some%20web%20development%20projects.%20I%20found%20a%20common%20problem%20with%20starting%20several%20new%20projects%20across%20different%20frameworks%20and%20runtimes%20is%20that%20I've%20been%20constantly%20looking%20up%20their%20docs%20online%20or%20my%20own%20notes%20on%20setting%20new%20projects%20up.%0A%0AI%20decided%20it%20was%20finally%20time%20to%20start%20doing%20a%20little%20automation%20with%20shell%20scripts.%0A%0AThe%20first%20runtime-framework%20combination%20I'm%20working%20with%20is%20Node%20and%20Express.%20The%20script%20asks%20for%20the%20project%20name%20so%20that%20it%20could%20create%20a%20directory%20in%20my%20usual%20projects%20directory.%20It%20then%20goes%20through%20the%20motions%20of%20running%20the%20standard%20%60npm%60%20or%20%60yarn%60%20project%20initialisation.%20It%20also%20installs%20the%20%60nodemon%60%20package%20so%20that%20Node%20could%20automatically%20restart%20the%20app%20whenever%20I%20make%20a%20change.%0A%0AIt%20works%20great%20for%20my%20standard%20Express%20backend%20project%20setup.%20However%20I%20plan%20on%20adding%20flags%20so%20that%20it%20could%20be%20more%20convenient%20to%20toggle%20adding%20additional%20packages%20like%20%60nodemon%60.%20Flags%20could%20play%20a%20larger%20role%20in%20the%20future%20when%20I%20automate%20the%20setup%20process%20for%20React%20and%20Vue%20projects%20(i.e.%20adding%20a%20router%20package,%20or%20the%20Material%20UI%20or%20Bootstrap%20packages).%0A%0AI'm%20also%20figuring%20out%20a%20frontend%20or%20interface%20to%20conveniently%20toggle%20various%20options%20in%20a%20single%20*view*%20rather%20than%20fiddling%20with%20flags%20and%20command%20line%20parameters.%20An%20%60ncurses%60%20text%20user%20interface%20was%20my%20initial%20choice,%20but%20I'm%20currently%20experimenting%20with%20an%20Electron%20app%20that%20would%20call%20the%20script%20and%20plug%20in%20the%20necessary%20flags.%0A%0AYou%20can%20take%20a%20look%20at%20the%20initial%20script%20on%20%5BGitHub%5D(https://github.com/csiew/boilerplate_generators).%20The%20script%20is%20currently%20designed%20for%20use%20on%20Debian-based%20Linux%20distributions.%20Support%20for%20macOS%20(and%20maybe%20Windows)%20will%20come%20a%20little%20later.%0A"
  }
]